{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I am a conductor,"},{"time":2000,"text":"and I'm here today"},{"time":4000,"text":"to talk to you about trust."},{"time":6000,"text":"My job depends upon it."},{"time":9000,"text":"There has to be, between me and the orchestra,"},{"time":11000,"text":"an unshakable bond of trust,"},{"time":13000,"text":"born out of mutual respect,"},{"time":16000,"text":"through which we can spin a musical narrative"},{"time":19000,"text":"that we all believe in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"Now in the old days, conducting, music making,"},{"time":24000,"text":"was less about trust and more, frankly, about coercion."},{"time":27000,"text":"Up to and around about the Second World War,"},{"time":29000,"text":"conductors were invariably dictators --"},{"time":31000,"text":"these tyrannical figures"},{"time":33000,"text":"who would rehearse, not just the orchestra as a whole, but individuals within it,"},{"time":36000,"text":"within an inch of their lives."},{"time":39000,"text":"But I'm happy to say now that the world has moved on,"},{"time":41000,"text":"music has moved on with it."},{"time":43000,"text":"We now have a more democratic view and way of making music --"},{"time":46000,"text":"a two-way street."},{"time":48000,"text":"I, as the conductor, have to come to the rehearsal with a cast-iron sense"},{"time":51000,"text":"of the outer architecture of that music,"},{"time":54000,"text":"within which there is then immense personal freedom"},{"time":57000,"text":"for the members of the orchestra to shine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"For myself, of course,"},{"time":61000,"text":"I have to completely trust my body language."},{"time":65000,"text":"That's all I have at the point of sale."},{"time":67000,"text":"It's silent gesture."},{"time":69000,"text":"I can hardly bark out instructions while we're playing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, the Scottish Ensemble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165000,"text":"So in order for all this to work,"},{"time":167000,"text":"obviously I have got to be in a position of trust."},{"time":169000,"text":"I have to trust the orchestra,"},{"time":171000,"text":"and, even more crucially, I have to trust myself."},{"time":173000,"text":"Think about it: when you're in a position of not trusting,"},{"time":175000,"text":"what do you do?"},{"time":177000,"text":"You overcompensate."},{"time":179000,"text":"And in my game, that means you overgesticulate."},{"time":181000,"text":"You end up like some kind of rabid windmill."},{"time":183000,"text":"And the bigger your gesture gets,"},{"time":185000,"text":"the more ill-defined, blurry"},{"time":187000,"text":"and, frankly, useless it is to the orchestra."},{"time":189000,"text":"You become a figure of fun. There's no trust anymore, only ridicule."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192000,"text":"And I remember at the beginning of my career,"},{"time":194000,"text":"again and again, on these dismal outings with orchestras,"},{"time":196000,"text":"I would be going completely insane on the podium,"},{"time":199000,"text":"trying to engender a small scale crescendo really,"},{"time":201000,"text":"just a little upsurge in volume."},{"time":203000,"text":"Bugger me, they wouldn't give it to me."},{"time":205000,"text":"I spent a lot of time in those early years"},{"time":207000,"text":"weeping silently in dressing rooms."},{"time":209000,"text":"And how futile seemed the words of advice to me"},{"time":212000,"text":"from great British veteran conductor Sir Colin Davis"},{"time":214000,"text":"who said, \"Conducting, Charles,"},{"time":216000,"text":"is like holding a small bird in your hand."},{"time":218000,"text":"If you hold it too tightly, you crush it."},{"time":221000,"text":"If you hold it too loosely, it flies away.\""},{"time":224000,"text":"I have to say, in those days, I couldn't really even find the bird."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"Now a fundamental"},{"time":229000,"text":"and really viscerally important experience for me, in terms of music,"},{"time":232000,"text":"has been my adventures in South Africa,"},{"time":234000,"text":"the most dizzyingly musical country on the planet in my view,"},{"time":237000,"text":"but a country which, through its musical culture,"},{"time":239000,"text":"has taught me one fundamental lesson:"},{"time":242000,"text":"that through music making"},{"time":244000,"text":"can come deep levels"},{"time":246000,"text":"of fundamental life-giving trust."},{"time":249000,"text":"Back in 2000, I had the opportunity to go to South Africa"},{"time":252000,"text":"to form a new opera company."},{"time":254000,"text":"So I went out there, and I auditioned,"},{"time":256000,"text":"mainly in rural township locations, right around the country."},{"time":258000,"text":"I heard about 2,000 singers"},{"time":260000,"text":"and pulled together a company"},{"time":262000,"text":"of 40 of the most jaw-droppingly amazing young performers,"},{"time":265000,"text":"the majority of whom were black,"},{"time":267000,"text":"but there were a handful of white performers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269000,"text":"Now it emerged early on in the first rehearsal period"},{"time":271000,"text":"that one of those white performers"},{"time":273000,"text":"had, in his previous incarnation,"},{"time":275000,"text":"been a member of the South African police force."},{"time":277000,"text":"And in the last years of the old regime,"},{"time":279000,"text":"he would routinely be detailed to go into the township"},{"time":282000,"text":"to aggress the community."},{"time":284000,"text":"Now you can imagine what this knowledge did to the temperature in the room,"},{"time":287000,"text":"the general atmosphere."},{"time":289000,"text":"Let's be under no illusions."},{"time":291000,"text":"In South Africa, the relationship most devoid of trust"},{"time":294000,"text":"is that between a white policeman"},{"time":296000,"text":"and the black community."},{"time":298000,"text":"So how do we recover from that, ladies and gentlemen?"},{"time":300000,"text":"Simply through singing."},{"time":302000,"text":"We sang, we sang,"},{"time":305000,"text":"we sang,"},{"time":307000,"text":"and amazingly new trust grew,"},{"time":309000,"text":"and indeed friendship blossomed."},{"time":311000,"text":"And that showed me such a fundamental truth,"},{"time":313000,"text":"that music making and other forms of creativity"},{"time":316000,"text":"can so often go to places"},{"time":318000,"text":"where mere words cannot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321000,"text":"So we got some shows off the ground. We started touring them internationally."},{"time":323000,"text":"One of them was \"Carmen.\""},{"time":325000,"text":"We then thought we'd make a movie of \"Carmen,\""},{"time":327000,"text":"which we recorded and shot outside on location"},{"time":329000,"text":"in the township outside Cape Town called Khayelitsha."},{"time":331000,"text":"The piece was sung entirely in Xhosa,"},{"time":333000,"text":"which is a beautifully musical language, if you don't know it."},{"time":336000,"text":"It's called \"U-Carmen e-Khayelitsha\" --"},{"time":338000,"text":"literally \"Carmen of Khayelitsha.\""},{"time":340000,"text":"I want to play you a tiny clip of it now"},{"time":342000,"text":"for no other reason than to give you proof positive"},{"time":344000,"text":"that there is nothing tiny about South African music making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":420000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":427000,"text":"Something which I find utterly enchanting"},{"time":430000,"text":"about South African music making"},{"time":432000,"text":"is that it's so free."},{"time":434000,"text":"South Africans just make music really freely."},{"time":436000,"text":"And I think, in no small way,"},{"time":438000,"text":"that's due to one fundamental fact:"},{"time":440000,"text":"they're not bound to a system of notation."},{"time":442000,"text":"They don't read music."},{"time":444000,"text":"They trust their ears."},{"time":446000,"text":"You can teach a bunch of South Africans a tune in about five seconds flat."},{"time":449000,"text":"And then, as if by magic,"},{"time":451000,"text":"they will spontaneously improvise a load of harmony around that tune"},{"time":454000,"text":"because they can."},{"time":456000,"text":"Now those of us that live in the West, if I can use that term,"},{"time":459000,"text":"I think have a much more hidebound attitude or sense of music --"},{"time":462000,"text":"that somehow it's all about skill and systems."},{"time":465000,"text":"Therefore it's the exclusive preserve"},{"time":468000,"text":"of an elite, talented body."},{"time":470000,"text":"And yet, ladies and gentlemen, every single one of us on this planet"},{"time":473000,"text":"probably engages with music on a daily basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"And if I can broaden this out for a second,"},{"time":478000,"text":"I'm willing to bet that every single one of you sitting in this room"},{"time":481000,"text":"would be happy to speak with acuity, with total confidence,"},{"time":483000,"text":"about movies, probably about literature."},{"time":486000,"text":"But how many of you would be able to make a confident assertion"},{"time":489000,"text":"about a piece of classical music?"},{"time":492000,"text":"Why is this?"},{"time":494000,"text":"And what I'm going to say to you now"},{"time":496000,"text":"is I'm just urging you to get over"},{"time":498000,"text":"this supreme lack of self-confidence,"},{"time":500000,"text":"to take the plunge, to believe that you can trust your ears,"},{"time":503000,"text":"you can hear some of the fundamental muscle tissue,"},{"time":505000,"text":"fiber, DNA,"},{"time":507000,"text":"what makes a great piece of music great."},{"time":510000,"text":"I've got a little experiment I want to try with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"Did you know"},{"time":514000,"text":"that TED is a tune?"},{"time":516000,"text":"A very simple tune based on three notes -- T, E, D."},{"time":519000,"text":"Now hang on a minute."},{"time":521000,"text":"I know you're going to say to me, \"T doesn't exist in music.\""},{"time":524000,"text":"Well ladies and gentlemen, there's a time-honored system,"},{"time":526000,"text":"which composers have been using for hundreds of years,"},{"time":528000,"text":"which proves actually that it does."},{"time":531000,"text":"If I sing you a musical scale: A, B, C, D, E, F, G --"},{"time":535000,"text":"and I just carry on with the next set of letters in the alphabet, same scale:"},{"time":538000,"text":"H, I, J, K, L, M, N,"},{"time":541000,"text":"O, P, Q, R, S, T -- there you go."},{"time":543000,"text":"T, see it's the same as F in music."},{"time":545000,"text":"So T is F."},{"time":547000,"text":"So T, E, D is the same as F, E, D."},{"time":549000,"text":"Now that piece of music that we played at the start of this session"},{"time":552000,"text":"had enshrined in its heart"},{"time":554000,"text":"the theme, which is TED."},{"time":556000,"text":"Have a listen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":566000,"text":"Do you hear it?"},{"time":568000,"text":"Or do I smell some doubt in the room?"},{"time":570000,"text":"Okay, we'll play it for you again now,"},{"time":572000,"text":"and we're going to highlight, we're going to poke out the T, E, D."},{"time":575000,"text":"If you'll pardon the expression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"Oh my goodness me, there it was loud and clear, surely."},{"time":588000,"text":"I think we should make this even more explicit."},{"time":589000,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, it's nearly time for tea."},{"time":591000,"text":"Would you reckon you need to sing for your tea, I think?"},{"time":593000,"text":"I think we need to sing for our tea."},{"time":595000,"text":"We're going to sing those three wonderful notes: T, E, D."},{"time":598000,"text":"Will you have a go for me?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":600000,"text":"Audience: T, E, D."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602000,"text":"Charles Hazlewood: Yeah, you sound a bit more like cows really than human beings."},{"time":605000,"text":"Shall we try that one again?"},{"time":607000,"text":"And look, if you're adventurous, you go up the octave."},{"time":609000,"text":"T, E, D."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"Audience: T, E, D."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613000,"text":"CH: Once more with vim. (Audience: T, E, D.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":616000,"text":"There I am like a bloody windmill again, you see."},{"time":618000,"text":"Now we're going to put that in the context of the music."},{"time":621000,"text":"The music will start, and then at a signal from me, you will sing that."},{"time":626000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":638000,"text":"One more time,"},{"time":640000,"text":"with feeling, ladies and gentlemen."},{"time":642000,"text":"You won't make the key otherwise."},{"time":645000,"text":"Well done, ladies and gentlemen."},{"time":647000,"text":"It wasn't a bad debut for the TED choir,"},{"time":650000,"text":"not a bad debut at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653000,"text":"Now there's a project that I'm initiating at the moment"},{"time":655000,"text":"that I'm very excited about and wanted to share with you,"},{"time":657000,"text":"because it is all about changing perceptions,"},{"time":659000,"text":"and, indeed, building a new level of trust."},{"time":662000,"text":"The youngest of my children was born with cerebral palsy,"},{"time":665000,"text":"which as you can imagine,"},{"time":667000,"text":"if you don't have an experience of it yourself,"},{"time":669000,"text":"is quite a big thing to take on board."},{"time":671000,"text":"But the gift that my gorgeous daughter has given me,"},{"time":674000,"text":"aside from her very existence,"},{"time":676000,"text":"is that it's opened my eyes to a whole stretch of the community"},{"time":679000,"text":"that was hitherto hidden,"},{"time":681000,"text":"the community of disabled people."},{"time":683000,"text":"And I found myself looking at the Paralympics and thinking how incredible"},{"time":686000,"text":"how technology's been harnessed to prove beyond doubt"},{"time":689000,"text":"that disability is no barrier"},{"time":691000,"text":"to the highest levels of sporting achievement."},{"time":693000,"text":"Of course there's a grimmer side to that truth,"},{"time":695000,"text":"which is that it's actually taken decades for the world at large"},{"time":698000,"text":"to come to a position of trust,"},{"time":701000,"text":"to really believe that disability and sports can go together"},{"time":704000,"text":"in a convincing and interesting fashion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707000,"text":"So I find myself asking:"},{"time":709000,"text":"where is music in all of this?"},{"time":711000,"text":"You can't tell me that there aren't millions of disabled people,"},{"time":713000,"text":"in the U.K. alone,"},{"time":715000,"text":"with massive musical potential."},{"time":718000,"text":"So I decided to create a platform for that potential."},{"time":721000,"text":"It's going to be Britain's first ever"},{"time":723000,"text":"national disabled orchestra."},{"time":725000,"text":"It's called Paraorchestra."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727000,"text":"I'm going to show you a clip now"},{"time":729000,"text":"of the very first improvisation session that we had."},{"time":731000,"text":"It was a really extraordinary moment."},{"time":733000,"text":"Just me and four astonishingly gifted disabled musicians."},{"time":736000,"text":"Normally when you improvise --"},{"time":739000,"text":"and I do it all the time around the world --"},{"time":741000,"text":"there's this initial period of horror,"},{"time":743000,"text":"like everyone's too frightened to throw the hat into the ring,"},{"time":745000,"text":"an awful pregnant silence."},{"time":747000,"text":"Then suddenly, as if by magic, bang! We're all in there"},{"time":749000,"text":"and it's complete bedlam. You can't hear anything."},{"time":751000,"text":"No one's listening. No one's trusting."},{"time":753000,"text":"No one's responding to each other."},{"time":756000,"text":"Now in this room with these four disabled musicians,"},{"time":758000,"text":"within five minutes"},{"time":760000,"text":"a rapt listening, a rapt response"},{"time":762000,"text":"and some really insanely beautiful music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"(Video) (Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"Nicholas:: My name's Nicholas McCarthy."},{"time":777000,"text":"I'm 22, and I'm a left-handed pianist."},{"time":779000,"text":"And I was born without my left hand -- right hand."},{"time":782000,"text":"Can I do that one again?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":785000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":792000,"text":"Lyn: When I'm making music,"},{"time":794000,"text":"I feel like a pilot in the cockpit flying an airplane."},{"time":797000,"text":"I become alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":810000,"text":"Clarence: I would rather be able to play an instrument again"},{"time":813000,"text":"than walk."},{"time":815000,"text":"There's so much joy and things"},{"time":817000,"text":"I could get from playing an instrument and performing."},{"time":821000,"text":"It's removed some of my paralysis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":840000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":847000,"text":"CH: I only wish that some of those musicians were here with us today,"},{"time":850000,"text":"so you could see at firsthand how utterly extraordinary they are."},{"time":853000,"text":"Paraorchestra is the name of that project."},{"time":855000,"text":"If any of you thinks you want to help me in any way"},{"time":857000,"text":"to achieve what is a fairly impossible and implausible dream still at this point,"},{"time":860000,"text":"please let me know."},{"time":862000,"text":"Now my parting shot"},{"time":864000,"text":"comes courtesy of the great Joseph Haydn,"},{"time":866000,"text":"wonderful Austrian composer in the second half of the 18th century --"},{"time":869000,"text":"spent the bulk of his life"},{"time":871000,"text":"in the employ of Prince Nikolaus Esterhazy, along with his orchestra."},{"time":874000,"text":"Now this prince loved his music,"},{"time":877000,"text":"but he also loved the country castle that he tended to reside in most of the time,"},{"time":880000,"text":"which is just on the Austro-Hungarian border,"},{"time":882000,"text":"a place called Esterhazy --"},{"time":884000,"text":"a long way from the big city of Vienna."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886000,"text":"Now one day in 1772,"},{"time":888000,"text":"the prince decreed that the musicians' families,"},{"time":890000,"text":"the orchestral musicians' families,"},{"time":892000,"text":"were no longer welcome in the castle."},{"time":894000,"text":"They weren't allowed to stay there anymore; they had to be returned to Vienna --"},{"time":897000,"text":"as I say, an unfeasibly long way away in those days."},{"time":900000,"text":"You can imagine, the musicians were disconsolate."},{"time":904000,"text":"Haydn remonstrated with the prince, but to no avail."},{"time":907000,"text":"So given the prince loved his music,"},{"time":909000,"text":"Haydn thought he'd write a symphony to make the point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912000,"text":"And we're going to play just the very tail end of this symphony now."},{"time":915000,"text":"And you'll see the orchestra in a kind of sullen revolt."},{"time":918000,"text":"I'm pleased to say, the prince did take the tip"},{"time":920000,"text":"from the orchestral performance,"},{"time":922000,"text":"and the musicians were reunited with their families."},{"time":924000,"text":"But I think it sums up my talk rather well, this,"},{"time":927000,"text":"that where there is trust,"},{"time":929000,"text":"there is music -- by extension life."},{"time":932000,"text":"Where there is no trust,"},{"time":934000,"text":"the music quite simply withers away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1131000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}